助教資訊 Contact with Tutor


學習規範 Course Policy
Attendence in every class is expected. If a student must miss a class due to illness, accident, or family crisis, she/he has to notify the instructor before class via e-mail or voice mail. For each missed class, a  make-up paper will be required. The paper should be a 2-page learning summary on the topic of the missed class. Studnets who missed the class are responsible for acquiring notes and announcements from their classmates. 

Paper / Presentation
Students will form 8 groups to prepare the AA papers amd the final presentation/paper.
- Acticity analysis paper (AA paper)
Each group will choose one daily activity to write an activity analysis report. This AA paper is due on the 10th week of the class.
- Final presentation/paper
Eeach group will choose either 1) one topic related to current OT issues (in practice, policy, in research… etc.) based on their interest, or 2) one particular population who commonly recieved OT service (refer  to OT Bible for common conditions).
The chosen topic with learning goals for the final presentation should be posted on the Moodle by the 13th week of the class. The final oral presentation will be in the 17th week of the class. And the written paper will be due on the 18th week of the class.
Stuednts will conduct a 8-minute oral presentation, followed by a 4-minute discussion. The format of the oral presentation is open. The final written paper should incorporat the feedbacks from the discussion of the oral presentation.
The written paper must be TYPED, double-spaced unless otherwise indicated. Please upload your paper via Moodle.  Please be aware that poor wording or typo will compromise the scores regardless of its content. Five points will be deducted each day for late submission after the dealine, unless an extension has been provided.

Plagiarism
Please document all sources of information taken from texts, handouts, sample assignments, internet… etc. Failure to do so may result in disciplinary action. Plagiarism includes cutting and pasting information from websites, not identifying where ideas have come from, taking from another student’s work and more.      

