Cultivate Innovative and Leadership Abilities in order to Develop Therapeutic Skills and Professional Research 

課程概述 Course Description
       簡介職能治療的發展與專業組織，倫理及其領域和功能。 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Define occupational therapy.Appreciate the history of the profession.Identify the values, beliefs, and practice of the profession.Describe the roles of occupational therapists and the therapeutic processes.Develop a sense of interest and commitment to the profession. 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Course orientation and overview of OT2History of OT3Philosophical base and values in OT; Roles/responsibilities/relationship of OT practitioners4Current issues and emerging practice areas;Treatment settings5OT Practice Framework6Activity analysis (AA)/synthesis (grading & adapting)7Theory, model of practice, and frames of reference8OT process: evaluation, intervention, and outcomes9Intervention modalities10Midterm Examination (AA paper due)11Service management12Therapeutic Relationship13Clinical reasoning14Professional associations; Standards and scopes of practice15AOTA code of ethics;Regulation of OT in Taiwan16ICF and Terms from Occupational Science17Presentation on Occupational Therapy Issues or Common Conditions18Final Examination (final paper due) 

